- PARAR OGG E INICIAR - CALIFORNIA
- VERIFICAR HEALTHCHECK DO GSLB - DALLAS
- PARAR BACKUP

SWITCH OVER
 
OKL2GT (primary database): 10.184.42.25
OKL2TB (standby database): 10.186.38.112
 
 
P.s.: Verifique se há ogg plugado. Caso sim, solicite a parada do ogg antes do switch over.
 
 
0. Criar blackout no primary e standby database
$ORACLE_BASE/product/agent135/agent_13.5.0.0.0/bin/emctl status blackout
$ORACLE_BASE/product/agent135/agent_13.5.0.0.0/bin/emctl start blackout SWITCHOVER -nodeLevel
$ORACLE_BASE/product/agent135/agent_13.5.0.0.0/bin/emctl status blackout
 
 
1. Abra o log do broker e alert log do banco de dados (primary e standby)
 
 
2. Verifique os serviços que estão ativos no primary database
$ srvctl status service -db OKL2GT -v
 
 
3. Verifique se há gaps de archivelog (rode nas duas instâncias)
set lines 400 
select dest_id, status, gap_status, ERROR from V$archive_dest_status where status<>'INACTIVE';
 
 
4. Alterar modo de proteção do banco de dados para MaxAvailability
$ dgmgrl /
DGMGRL> show configuration verbose
DGMGRL> edit database "OKL2GT" set property LogXptMode=SYNC;
Property "logxptmode" updated
DGMGRL> edit database "OKL2TB" set property LogXptMode=SYNC;
Property "logxptmode" updated
DGMGRL> edit configuration set protection mode as MaxAvailability;
Succeeded.
DGMGRL>
DGMGRL> validate database verbose OKL2GT;
DGMGRL> validate database verbose OKL2TB;
 
 
5. Force alguns switchs de logfile
SQL> alter system switch all logfile;

6. Execute o switch over (conectado no primary)
dgmgrl sys@OKL2GT_DGMGRL 
dgmgrl> show configuration verbose;
dgmgrl> switchover to OKL2TB;
 
 
7. Após a virada alterar modo de proteção do banco de dados para MaxPerformance
$ dgmgrl /
DGMGRL> show configuration verbose
DGMGRL> edit database "OKL2GT" set property LogXptMode=ASYNC;
Property "logxptmode" updated
DGMGRL> edit database "OKL2TB" set property LogXptMode=ASYNC;
Property "logxptmode" updated
DGMGRL> edit configuration set protection mode as MaxPerformance;
Succeeded.
DGMGRL>
DGMGRL> show configuration verbose;
DGMGRL> show database OKL2gt;
DGMGRL> show database OKL2tb;
DGMGRL> validate database verbose OKL2gt;
DGMGRL> validate database verbose OKL2tb;
 
 
8. Valide se o dns fez o chaveamento automático
nslookup cdbname.bd.intranet.pags
nslookup pdbname.bd.intranet.pags

nslookup OKL2.bd.intranet.pags

 
9. Solicitar validação das apps.
 
 
10. Remover blackout no primary e standby database
$ORACLE_BASE/product/agent135/agent_13.5.0.0.0/bin/emctl status blackout
$ORACLE_BASE/product/agent135/agent_13.5.0.0.0/bin/emctl stop blackout SWITCHOVER
$ORACLE_BASE/product/agent135/agent_13.5.0.0.0/bin/emctl status blackout


